<br>
I know 60's that won't go in there unless they have absolute confidence in their group support.<br>
<br>
Its gotten much worse (on the dangerous scale) now that the zone isn't camped at all.  However, as an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> exclusive</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> hunting ground for raids, it can't be matched - no contests on drops, no campers, etc.<br>
<br>
You can't safely invis into the back of the castle <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> unless</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> you luck out and there isn't an undead guard posted out in the main hall.  The only way you can 100% punch through with reliability is to have a high level (45+?) puller single pull the mobs in the hall out to an area where you can attack them cleanly or have multiple groups and serious crowd control (2+ enchanters w/ AOE mez up and ready).  The ambassador room just chain pulls too easily.  Thrar and his friends couldn't reliably fight through the hall without agroing the ambassador room at level 33-37.  That is principly why they left to go to the Tower of Frozen Shadow and Crystal Caverns.  They won't go back until the group as a whole is 40+.<br>
<br>
Some added complexities:  warping or &quot;ghosting&quot; patrols, idiots training the castle, etc, make this zone what it is.<br>
<br>
One thing that everyone going on a raid into a dungeon must be willing to deal with is party deaths and CRs.  It goes with the territory.  While it would be perfect to have a guild raid with no deaths, if we are looking for specific valuable drops or quest components, the &quot;risk&quot; involved is character death.  That's the way of the game.  It's how &quot;Risk vs. Reward&quot; is balanced.<br>
